<article>
	<div class="resNewsEmbed resNews">












	













	












<h1 class="title">Mattamy Athletic Centre and Toronto/Peel In-Person Programs to close November 23, 2020</h1>



<div class="date">November 20, 2020</div>


</div>

	<div class="content stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="ab32e1af-0c8c-4471-9e04-ab7dc866086f" >

    <p>Regretfully, following the Ontario government's announcement that Toronto and Peel will be returning to the 'Lockdown - Grey' level of the new <a href="https://www.ontario.ca/page/covid-19-response-framework-keeping-ontario-safe-and-open">COVID framework<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a> effective Monday, November 23 @ 12:01am, the Mattamy Athletic Centre and all in-person programs in the Toronto and Peel regions will close end of day this Sunday, November 22 until further notice.</p> 
<p>The importance of physical activity as a well-being and learning strategy remains a constant, and we encourage you to stay active while following public health guidelines. Ryerson programs still in operation after November 23 include:&nbsp;</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a href="/content/ryerson/recreation/move-everywhere-online.html#accordion-1599785719322-group-fitness--live-zoom-classes">Daily Live Group Fitness Classes on Zoom</a></li> 
 <li><a href="/content/ryerson/recreation/move-everywhere-online.html#accordion-1599785734722-on-demand-activities---classes">On-demand online programs</a> including <a href="/content/ryerson/recreation/programs/movement-breaks.html">Movement Breaks</a></li> 
 <li><a href="/content/ryerson/recreation/move-everywhere-neighbourhood.html#accordion-1599785719322-neighbourhood-movement-meetups">Neighbourhood Movement Meetups</a> outside the regions (Toronto/Peel) under lockdown</li> 
</ul> 
<p>As before, more information on refunds for staff/faculty memberships, upcoming first aid courses and other details will be shared next week.</p> 
<p>While the closure of MAC and some programs is difficult news, we are grateful for the collective efforts of our staff, students and members ensuring our programs and facilities have operated safely to date, with no recorded transmission of any infections.</p> 
<p>We will continue to share updates on programs and facilities via our website and @RURecreation social channels.</p> 
<p>#StayActive #StayWell #MoveEverywhere</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#ab32e1af-0c8c-4471-9e04-ab7dc866086f");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resImageText section">


























		<div class="thumbnail customStyle1" id="8b6c9496-dcb4-4de1-8c17-316629e68553">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6">
					
						<a class="imageOverlayLink" href="/recreation/move-everywhere-online/">
<img src="/content/dam/recreation/zoom-workout.jpg"/>



</a>   
					
				</div>
				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6">
				
						<div class="caption richtextContent">
	<h2>MOVE Everywhere: Online</h2> 
<p>The importance of regular physical activity and a sense of community connection are critical to our well-being and academic success.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>Whether live classes with us or pre-recorded content from elsewhere, Esports or Zoom meetups: Join us... And&nbsp;<em>MOVE!</em></p> 
<p>All programs are freely available to all Ryerson students.</p>
</div>  
						    
